http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/Free-shoes-for-students/article14013149.ece

In a bid to attract more students and contain school dropouts, West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee has sanctioned Rs 154 crore to provide school shoes free to all students of classes I to IV.“Our government has sanctioned Rs 154 crore for free distribution of shoes to students of classes I to IV,” Ms Banerjee said here on Wednesday.“On my way to ‘Mati Utsav’ in Burdwan district, I had met a group of children in a primary school. I was touched to see many of them barefoot. I immediately advised education department to take steps so that all primary school children get shoes,” the Chief Minister said.- PTI